name: Rich Menga
review: I use this primarily as a driving app on my Samsung Galaxy S7. It works, but there are a few things that are annoying. Collections (i.e. favorites) management is terrible. No way to sort collected places by nearest distance from current location or even alphabetically. No way to edit a place once se...Full ReviewI use this primarily as a driving app on my Samsung Galaxy S7. It works, but there are a few things that are annoying. Collections (i.e. favorites) management is terrible. No way to sort collected places by nearest distance from current location or even alphabetically. No way to edit a place once set, meaning you can't even rename a place after you save it. And in many instances you are not even allowed to set the name of the place when initially saving it. This leads to a same-name problem (such as two Targets, two Walmarts, etc.), and since you can't sort your collections list, two totally different locations look exactly the same in the same list, forcing you to load each individually and check just to see where they are. Different map themes are desperately needed because the two offered (day and night) do not have enough contrast for driving use, especially for day driving. The map lines and directional arrow also need to have thicker outlines. While the top and bottom bar text is done right with big, thick, bold fonts, the map itself does not get the same treatment where all street name text is tiny, road lines are skinny and proper contrast for driving use simply isn't there. Adjusting the phone's screen resolution, text size and screen zoom doesn't help with this at all (believe me, I tried). When using text-only directions while driving (start a route, tap top text bar to show full screen text directions), the list of directions does not update itself after taking a turn. After taking a turn, the last direction at top of the list should leave, and all directions scroll up to display the next turn at top of the list. This doesn't happen, making the text-only list while driving useless. If that list actually updated itself after each turn, this would be a *fantastic* feature. There should be a way to use Speed Alerts with visual cue only with no sound. Instead you have an "all or nothing" option where if enabled, over-limit speed turns red and a double-tone (which cannot be customized) is heard. It would be very nice to turn that sound off and only see the visual cue. When viewing a collected place's details, it should show everything, including the GPS coordinates. It doesn't. The only way to see a collected place's coordinates is to share it as a text message, and in the URL you actually see the coordinates there. Very wonky workaround just to get this info. There is the ability to creation a home location shortcut icon outside of the app by long pressing the home icon. This is great. Unfortunately, that's the only shortcut you can create. It would be nice to create a shortcut for any collected place.

If you don't have a connection it just crashes when trying to load - it has to be set to offline before it works... but crashing before it can load up to setup and use offline is infuriating. The main reason I use this app was fo...Full ReviewThis app used to be amazing. Now the offline functionality is rubbish. If you don't have a connection it just crashes when trying to load - it has to be set to offline before it works... but crashing before it can load up to setup and use offline is infuriating. The main reason I use this app was for that functionality. Only gets 2 stars as it's great when it works.

name: Russell Clark
review: Good mapping and route options but too many errors to justify five stars. I've not found away to do waypoints on the route and the display lacks Distance to Go. Updating the map on the app is easy but the changes don't seem to be incorporated into the map. Transit information has always been very ac...Full ReviewGood mapping and route options but too many errors to justify five stars. I've not found away to do waypoints on the route and the display lacks Distance to Go. Updating the map on the app is easy but the changes don't seem to be incorporated into the map. Transit information has always been very accurate. Best of all it's not Google.

name: John Coldwell
review: Hangs with "Waiting for GPS" at critical positions such as city centres or motorway junctions making the guidance almost impossible. I have downloaded maps so it should not be due to the app updating in real time. Only way to get it to work is by stopping the guidance and then restarting it which is...Full ReviewHangs with "Waiting for GPS" at critical positions such as city centres or motorway junctions making the guidance almost impossible. I have downloaded maps so it should not be due to the app updating in real time. Only way to get it to work is by stopping the guidance and then restarting it which is quite dangerous if you are in Germany and travelling at 160km/h or in a busy city centre where you have to be attentive to what is going on around you.

name: Paris Dimos
review: As already stated it does its job. I wish to reach satellite signal a bit faster (sometimes needs to restart before routing 1-2 times) but still great app. If there was a better connection with the signs at the motorway and the navigation screen, it would be perfect. I would actually buy it (but please do not introduce an unfriendly monthly/yearly payment method like Tom Tom...one time buying method is more honest)

name: Eric Imeson
review: A reliable navigation system with good guidance and accurate predictions of travel times and traffic delays. Maps are downloadable and cover nearly every country worldwide so mobile roaming data is not required when travelling abroad. All maps are free and contain loads of points of interest data. C...Full ReviewA reliable navigation system with good guidance and accurate predictions of travel times and traffic delays. Maps are downloadable and cover nearly every country worldwide so mobile roaming data is not required when travelling abroad. All maps are free and contain loads of points of interest data. Calculated routes for driving, cycling and walking are excellent but routes using public transport are not so reliable.

name: Mikhail Barkovsky
review: It would be great to choose the language for displaying the toponyms, or change the app language in general. We often travel to Russia and there it is much more practical to use the original Cyrillic writing. Also, navigating a route with several stops would be practical.

Features like postcode input are nice but since it has started screwing up like this, I can't give it a full rating.

review: It's slightly better than average especially considering it is free. IMO it is one of the best free navigation apps that work offline. The most annoying thing is that it cannot sort favorites b...Full ReviewIt's slightly better than average especially considering it is free. IMO it is one of the best free navigation apps that work offline. However, directions sometimes are confusing and it does not have "junction view" like now defunct Navigon. The most annoying thing is that it cannot sort favorites by distance from the current location. This feature was available on Windows phones. How difficult would it be to have this on Android? For example, when I look at my shopping favorite group, first stores that appear are from a different state because they were the first bookmarked: favorites are sorted in the order they are entered and it is impossible to re-order them either by distance or in alphabetical order.

review: At first I liked the clarity of the maps, but that was all! 1-It kept closing several times with in a few minutes, thank God I was trying it at home not on the road. 2-It doesn't show the different route options on the map like google, instead you see them as distance/time choices first., I need to ...Full ReviewAt first I liked the clarity of the maps, but that was all! 1-It kept closing several times with in a few minutes, thank God I was trying it at home not on the road. 2-It doesn't show the different route options on the map like google, instead you see them as distance/time choices first., I need to see the route also at the same time. 3-Couldn't name the locations easily, you have to pick a description from collect, then spend a long time trying to change that to your choice!

name: Mikele P
review: The app is awesome from every point of view: graphics, re-calculation speed, simplicity and offline maps with voice indications!!! name: Dennis Roth
review: Really love the offline features, but i think a couple more options would be lovely. So I started driving this year and I like to listen to music while doing so, but the constant voice prompts are really ennoying. Id like to see an options to turn them off completely, because with the current "optio...Full ReviewReally love the offline features, but i think a couple more options would be lovely. So I started driving this year and I like to listen to music while doing so, but the constant voice prompts are really ennoying. Id like to see an options to turn them off completely, because with the current "option" it resets every time you launch the app. So i have to uninstall it and get annoying pop ups and dont have the option of enabling it on the go (50mb download, making the offline maps obsolete^^) Also id like to see an option to avoid certain roads, e.g. i havent got a "vignette" for austria, so i cant use their highways. Also a start, via point x, destination would be nice. This could also serve as help for the before mentioned problem, since right now i have to start guidance to a point not on the highway first, when i reach it i have to pull over only to enter my final destination and check if it sends me over a highway. So like avoid highways for certain countries switch would be aswesome! Last improvement would be the search. If im currently in a city and just type in a street, i dont want to see an option across the country, but cant even see the street where im at until i type the cities name too. Same for searching cities that are close to me, if im in germany and type lindau i dont want to get guidance to some small town in switzerland, but id prefere the city in the country im currently at. While this sounds very negative now, it really isnt! I love the app, but i also know that it is hard for devs to improve something without getting exact feedback from the community. So there you go, and thanks for the great experience :)

review: I have been forced to leave Windows Mobile. Certain apps are at the core of my life. GPS is one since I travel a lot. Here Maps was a favorite before Microsoft adopted its framework. But now I find myself switching to Android for the first time in my life, not enthusiastically mind you. But Here WeGo seems to have most of what I need, but not all. Dist to Destination and Altitude, fix the minutes.

review: Better than Google maps.

name: Gabriel Skiver
review: I installed this app in order to store maps offline. the first thing it did upon installation was demand access to my GPS location, and would not allow me to access any of its features without granting location permission. I don't need another app to tell me where I am and track my location. I wante...Full ReviewI installed this app in order to store maps offline. the first thing it did upon installation was demand access to my GPS location, and would not allow me to access any of its features without granting location permission. I don't need another app to tell me where I am and track my location. I wanted maps that were not dependent on cell service, which this did not provide.

name: A Google user
review: This app is great thanks to its worldwide maps. Functionality is not ideal. Sometimes it's very hard to make it understand you are looking for a route with starting point other than current location. Then there's the collected places and their management which needs to be easier to use and edit. Navigation in general is very good and functional.

name: Ale? Schwartzman
review: not suitable for navigation in Europe. Very dangerous - i almost went the opposite way.

name: ¡kos Guly·s
review: Its better than Google. But be careful! E.g.: You drive, phone is on the windscreen, Here navigation runs. You get a call, speak to someone, call ends. But be careful! E.g.: You drive, phone is on the windscreen, Here navigation runs. You get a call, speak to someone, call ends. You expect, Here screen will come back, navigation will continue. But no, sometimes Here exits. (at 6GB RAM, ~50% free!) It stops to run! In this case, you may start to tap your phone automatically, meanwhile you may cause an accident and somebody may die.

name: Joey E Hoyt
review: Installed in Truck on Android Radio... Haven't Updated in Over a Year. name: Athena Huff-Sandstrom
review: Suddenly I keep getting "off the rails" messages, even if the transit planning was working literally minutes before, and it also happens with taxis (downtown Denver is definitely not a "taxi-free zone") the only remedy is to uninstall and reinstall the app, which is not particularly practical. What ...Full ReviewSuddenly I keep getting "off the rails" messages, even if the transit planning was working literally minutes before, and it also happens with taxis (downtown Denver is definitely not a "taxi-free zone") the only remedy is to uninstall and reinstall the app, which is not particularly practical. What is going on?! ETA: Thank you for the response - I look forward to restoring this rating to five stars!
reply:
Hi! We're aware of this issue and our developers are working on resolving it as soon as possible! For now please try reinstalling the application or send us an email to appsupport@here.com. Thank you!

HERE WeGo Support Team

name: A Google user
review: The old "Here" app used to be the greatest for offline navigation in my opinion. I particularly liked it when traveling in countries where roaming data costs were unreasonable, or when out of network coverage. it is still a great navigation package, very well designed. However, it no longer lets us ...Full ReviewThe old "Here" app used to be the greatest for offline navigation in my opinion. I particularly liked it when traveling in countries where roaming data costs were unreasonable, or when out of network coverage. it is still a great navigation package, very well designed. However, it no longer lets us store places unless we are logged in. I would have rather pay for a package which truly works offline, with no privacy compromises.

name: Ciel Azul
review: Regarding "Waiting for GPS" message: Try installing Google Maps, if same problem persists, it is due to ygps settings on Mediatek devices. Use engineer mode to enable "run in background" for ygps. This worked for me.

name: ¡ron Bagdi
review: Unreliable navigation. We wanted to use it on a roadtrip in Jordan. downloaded the maps prior to the trip. It turned out that the map was not detailed at all. We wanted to use it on a roadtrip in Jordan. downloaded the maps prior to the trip. It turned out that the map was not detailed at all. name: Richard Pullano
review: I have used this app for a number of years, in many countries and was thoroughly pleased. I've tried many options and I'm stumped so I'm relu...Full ReviewI have used this app for a number of years, in many countries and was thoroughly pleased. I was using an iPhone 6S and just changed to a Samsung S9 plus. it worked well with my Prius bluetooth initially and then the audio through my car radio quit. I've tried many options and I'm stumped so I'm reluctantly dropping it to try another. the phone portion still works but the audio for this app quit so it is not a viable and useable option for me anymore.

name: Ha Cuong
review: I used this map since Symbian. It was still good on Windows Mobile. A lot less features with Android or after every update. Still good for offline map and planning your trip on PC after you log in to your account

name: Wesley Robertson
review: I like it, but was let down twice recently. Went on long trips and chose a specific route to use offline, only for the app to take me on a different route that I wanted to avoid. Then also on the last trip on the return journey I only had 1 choice of routes instead of the 3 that I had at the start. ...Full ReviewI like it, but was let down twice recently. Went on long trips and chose a specific route to use offline, only for the app to take me on a different route that I wanted to avoid. Then also on the last trip on the return journey I only had 1 choice of routes instead of the 3 that I had at the start. Also had a very strange start to a route that was far from the quickest or most convenient to get onto the motorway. Give us more routes and stick to them, please!!!

name: Mohsin Raza
review: Excellent App Recommended.

name: Gino Lee
review: of the 4-5 offline nav apps i've tried, by far the best! none of the others could take a simple address. suggestion: for the default voice, default to one that speaks the street names. also, have the option to turn off the display during nav, to save power, as i mostly listen to it as i'm driving. a...Full Reviewof the 4-5 offline nav apps i've tried, by far the best! none of the others could take a simple address. suggestion: for the default voice, default to one that speaks the street names. also, have the option to turn off the display during nav, to save power, as i mostly listen to it as i'm driving. also have a "repeat last instruction" button, as i may have missed the last instruction.. all on all, i'm happy with it so far!

name: Kha Nguyen
review: A good idea, nice feature and user interface. Horrible implementation, app crashes very often, while using to look for direction, and while navigating. GPS is not reliable. I really want this app to be good because it is the only nice alternative to Google Maps, and I have given this app many chances, install, then uninstall, then reinstall. Please focus on app reliability first.

name: A Google user

review: Best and free navigation tools and offline map, i always had problems of google map when traveling abroad when 3g connection is not stable. name: Chris B
review: The navigation's great. Turns come up maybe a second earlier than when you actually have to turn. My only real gripes are that the voice guidance keeps trying to turn itself back on, the voice module...Full ReviewThe navigation's great. Turns come up maybe a second earlier than when you actually have to turn. Location icons (such as gas stations, hotels, etc.) could be a little bigger, but still very useful. My only real gripes are that the voice guidance keeps trying to turn itself back on, the voice module re-downloads after updates when I delete it, and it crashes if I leave it in the background for too long.

review: I really like this app... The navigation is easy and essential... Only the elements that are really necessary... This provides you a pleasant driving and gets you to the point without loosing time...

name: Verandi Soldusty
review: For local trips it's fine but on longer journeys that mean Sat-nav is a must it fails. name: Loukas Sideris
review: Old versions had a list with nearby points of interests. Now I can't find it. name: Lydia Primich
review: Great app, due to its options. I find myself in rural areas with spotty service so being able to download street maps of single states or countries is an amazing option. I find myself in rural areas with spotty service so being able to download street maps of single states or countries is an amazing option. In addition, when using active navigation, you can set the app to ding if you speed. Again, since I am often driving through small towns with low speed limits, bored cops and out of state tags, I love this feature.

name: Sandra Hall
review: used for the first time today got me to my destination okay but on the way back seemed to be working okay for the first 2 mins then said waiting for GPS whilst I was on the move. I thought it was going to be like Here Drive that I had on my previous Nokia Windows phone which was 100% reliable. Sadly this was not. Very disappointing.

name: Davec iServices
review: Has some nice features like different voices, save to SD card, gives you multiple routes to choose from. Unfortunately not many POIs for where I live. Map picture is also very basic lacking any details like building shapes. Your destination is the blob on the road.

name: John Hoit
review: So much wrong here and I have yet to find out if this actually is useful. First, it provides ONLY a Facebook login option (other than a regular email address), no Google login, or as we need to progress to, MeWe. When I created an account, they required that I enter my full exact birthday. WHY? Beca...Full ReviewSo much wrong here and I have yet to find out if this actually is useful. First, it provides ONLY a Facebook login option (other than a regular email address), no Google login, or as we need to progress to, MeWe. When I created an account, they required that I enter my full exact birthday. WHY? Because their Terms of Service state that you MUST be 16 or older to use their product. What is with that? Suspicious for sure. Are they collecting data to sell? On the phone app, if you click the About button to see who you are dealing with, they don't identify by name on the surface. You have to dig down to find an actual name of the company. It's like they are afraid of exposure. If I find this is actually worthy of praise, I'll come back and update. Until then, trust is low especially when Facebook is their main login option.

name: Steve Davis
review: Should be 5 stars, some glaring issues with it. It most often refuses to load, I have to close it and reopen it several times, even letting it go will not bring it up, or sometimes brings it up with the locator but no map. After several years of use I've had to uninstall and reinstall this app to ge...Full ReviewShould be 5 stars, some glaring issues with it. It most often refuses to load, I have to close it and reopen it several times, even letting it go will not bring it up, or sometimes brings it up with the locator but no map. After several years of use I've had to uninstall and reinstall this app to get it to work again, it freezes and stops loading till I do. More than once I had to give up and use Google maps instead. Map updates are inconsistent, I have this on 2 phones, once in a while I see there are updates, but only on ONE phone (both android). This time BOTH said there were map updates, I downloaded them, finished and the next day an APP update, and ONE of the phones said there was a map update. I know this is free but it needs to be a lot more stable for it to be back to 5 stars.

name: Nina Jajszczyk
review: I love it. Just one idea to suggest that would make this app absolutely brilliant: Why don't you introduce the alarm function that would remind to leave the bus, tram one stop before leaving? name: Tom Wilkinson

Deleted the app today & reinstalled with a fresh download yet again in the hope it might be more reliable Getting tiresome now. Reverted to paper maps again!

name: Jey C
review: Great navigation, and offline maps helps cut down roaming data when I am traveling. Does it check for updates (especially short term changes like roadworks/construction) or rely 100% on potentially stale maps?

name: Prasad P
review: Good app with a lot of untapped potential. 1. For generation navigation, doesn't really offer anything over Google maps (except for saving data if you are on a limited data option) but if the developers add a road trip planning feature with an option of navigation, none of the other apps that I know...Full ReviewGood app with a lot of untapped potential. 1. For generation navigation, doesn't really offer anything over Google maps (except for saving data if you are on a limited data option) but if the developers add a road trip planning feature with an option of navigation, none of the other apps that I know of, offer such a feature. (You can plan trip in Google My Maps but won't allow navigation option). 2. Will be great if an option is offered to import kml, kmz or gpx file navigation. 3. Offer an option to import addresses to the collection from a text file. At the moment, I have to search every address and add to the collection one by one. Text import feature can check the addresses for their validity at the time of import. Also add an option to sort the addresses. 4. Not exactly sure if red camera detection is offered. If it does, any option to update those cameras? 5. Pls offer an option to have your own POIs (for offline use). 6. Offer an option NOT to re-route. 7. If you can integrate GasBuddy data for fuel, it will be awesome. If you do, allow to sort the fuel by brand/top tier. Will update the review if required.

name: c3
review: Much neater map viewing than Google. In particular: why do I need a huge, un-dismissable, waste-of-screen-space card showing just the address of the building I'm exploring the interior of?

name: Gavin Smith
review: I so want to like this app and use it on my android head unit in the van. It looks nice, is simple to use and generally picks routes well. Unfortunately, when it wants to download maps, it requires you to download the entire England map at 1.1gb - Then when it does updates it seems to download a lar...Full ReviewI so want to like this app and use it on my android head unit in the van. It looks nice, is simple to use and generally picks routes well. Unfortunately, when it wants to download maps, it requires you to download the entire England map at 1.1gb - Then when it does updates it seems to download a large file again. Even on a home wifi that would be problematic if there are frequent updates, but on a mobile data plan that's simply unacceptable. Given that I use it for about 50 miles around me the fact that isn't an option to limit the map download makes it unusable in the car - It also doesn't let me sign in for some reason (my car head unit has a unusual resolution and I think it misses showing the login button. It then randomly turns on a voice (and forces you to download one) even when I never want voice navigation in the car. Finally, it won't let you start up in driving mode, which would be very handy in a car head unit for when you don't want to input a destination but do want traffic on your route displayed. Such a shame but II will have to keep looking. If this had reasonable map download/updates, and a simple way to send destinations from the online maps, it would truly be a better alternative than Google

review: Navigation is really working good and maps are good. Why I do not give a 5 star rating is because the app does not allow landscape mode when entering the address, only when navigating. name: Dmitry XOMYT
review: First, when exiting HERE with a back button, it stays in background. With GPS eating your battery. Not fun abroad after 3h walk do not have your battery anymore. But to close HERE you need to go to all apps and fr...Full ReviewFirst, when exiting HERE with a back button, it stays in background. With GPS eating your battery. And still no multipoint itinerary or a search while you follow the GPS.

name: Mike Bruyneel
review: Much beter than Google maps. Especially when navigating in cities. I like that when I have to turn in a street, Here tells me "2nd on the right" instead of "turn right into "street name"". name: Hamman Samuel
review: Arguably the best alternative to Google Maps. Gives accurate search results for most local businesses, including phone and hours, and allows natural text searches. Also needs better Favorite locations management, current Collections options are cumbersome

name: Jason Dagless
review: Usually great however has a annoying and potentially dangerous bug that if two routes or more are available, if you choose one route it will constantly try to push you to another route even if the roads are dangerous or unsuitable. This means lots of second guessing and turning around when you find ...Full ReviewUsually great however has a annoying and potentially dangerous bug that if two routes or more are available, if you choose one route it will constantly try to push you to another route even if the roads are dangerous or unsuitable. This means lots of second guessing and turning around when you find the damn software has changed your route. Please let us lock the route we pick.

name: wood n
review: FAIL.the theory of the app is great with its ability to send directions to my watch, but the slightest gps signal deviation causes the app to stop providing directions. name: Tyrone Black
review: An option for offline maps is good. But it only works in theory. If you're looking for offline navigation: please use another map app. This one will get you very lost guaranteed. If you're looking for offline navigation: please use another map app. This one will get you very lost guaranteed. We had another map open but, HERE WeGo would repeatedly tell us to turn, (sometimes down dirt roads) although we had 16km before we needed to turn at all. If you want it for reference and you are able to navigate using the map yourself, then it's a great app. Just DON'T RELY on its own navigation. Its Awful.

name: Aussie witch
review: worked fine for a few years then stopped working could never connect to gps even tho it was on ..just redownloaded it hopefully it works now if not i wont be a happy camper

name: Leonard Frankel
review: Absolutely useless. Constantly crashes, for no apparent reason. God help you if you're trying to use it to navigate while in your car/on bike/whatever, because chances are it'll just crash five minutes into your journey. Pro: not Google. Con: barely works.

name: Mac Saxe
review: until a few months ago this was easily my favourite app, used all the time - after the last couple updates it cannot find any routes without an internet connection even if you eant to go one street away. then when you do get a wifi signal it finds the route, but as soon as you set off it either forg...Full Reviewuntil a few months ago this was easily my favourite app, used all the time - after the last couple updates it cannot find any routes without an internet connection even if you eant to go one street away. then when you do get a wifi signal it finds the route, but as soon as you set off it either forgets the route, loses where it thinks you are or plain freezes - and i guarantee it does this at complex moments when you really REALLY need to know where to go. Unreliable and dangerous app.

The only improvement to this already good app is visual lane by lane guidance like google maps has, the voice guidance gives it corectly but when driving in multilane busy cities the visual guidance is the better 1.

name: Wynter Munroe
review: great for directions if you are someone like me who even using a map can be directionally challenged at the top of the screen it tells me more simply what to do forward left or right and exactly when to do it. for busing it ottawa it at least tells me what buses are in the area and when they next co...Full Reviewgreat for directions if you are someone like me who even using a map can be directionally challenged at the top of the screen it tells me more simply what to do forward left or right and exactly when to do it. for busing it ottawa it at least tells me what buses are in the area and when they next come including if they have a delay and by how long. and love the offline part i dont put data on my phone i never need to worry about using my map like most that need internet.

review: Free offline maps, mostly accurate, and for many if not all countries. That's the positive. name: lost rebels

The local driving style is not the Euro/USA style, but rather what works to get you moving.

name: N.W. Shannon
review: I first started using Here WeGo on Nokia phones probably 7 years ago. I have Collections for holidays I've taken over the years (except for Japan!). name: Frank T
review: Recently, when I tried updating the data for the Entire Europe the Apps crashed and cannot be loaded. Even when I delete & re-install the Apps the Apps still crashed when I set the default data location to SD card. The only way that I could make the Apps work again was to manually delete the data on...Full ReviewRecently, when I tried updating the data for the Entire Europe the Apps crashed and cannot be loaded. Even when I delete & re-install the Apps the Apps still crashed when I set the default data location to SD card. The only way that I could make the Apps work again was to manually delete the data on my SD card and download all the maps again. My advice to anyone using this Apps to delete your old maps data and reload the maps rather than to update your maps. Recently I had some problems with the apps when one of the major road was blocked in Germany - the apps keeps redirecting me back to the blocked road. In the end I had to switch off the auto navigation and used the apps as a map to by-pass the road block. I would have given it 5 stars if not for the fact that maps storage defaults to phone memory instead of ExtSdCard - and the only way it seems that it can be moved to the SD card is to delete the maps, set download to ExtSdCard and download the maps all over again (and that could take quite some time as the files are huge) - Plus the 44MB+ app cannot be moved to the SD card, making it not suitable for phones with small internal memory.

name: Michael Joyce
review: I have installed the Here WeGo GPS app on a number of smart phones with flawless operation..... simple to use and very accurate.   In January, 2019 I installed a Pumpkin Android 8.1 Car Radio-Navigation device in my car.    Here WeGo installed with no problems and I used it until I received a messag...Full ReviewI have installed the Here WeGo GPS app on a number of smart phones with flawless operation..... simple to use and very accurate.   In January, 2019 I installed a Pumpkin Android 8.1 Car Radio-Navigation device in my car.    Here WeGo installed with no problems and I used it until I received a message that there was a June 5 update.   I updated my telephone with no problems and then my Car Nav.   Here WeGo would not open.   After doing all of the usual maintenance activities like uninstall-reinstall, cleaning of caches, etc, there was no joy.   I contacted the WeGo company.  I promptly received an email with help suggestions that I had done before contacting them.   Finally, the representative told me that Here WeGo was designed for smart phones ONLY and was not designed for use in a dedicated car navigation system., and would not be available for more assistance.     I believe this is a valuable GPS Nav app and I also believe that there is a simple solution to my problem.   When this app works, my opinion is that it is one of the best.   But with Android devices becoming very common, the company's attitude should change.   I change my rating to 1star.

Hi,
The reason we are asking permission for the app to access the phone dialing function is the following: Some POIs - like restaurants - provide a phone number in the app. We give the user the possibility to call directly by clicking on the phone number. This has always been something Here has claimed is not possible but my last windows phone was able to use voice navigation on my previous car when connected to Bluetooth. reply:
Hello,
The reason we are asking permission for the app to access the phone call option is indeed the answer provided by our Customer Support Agents: Some POIs - like restaurants - provide a phone number. We give the user the possibility to call directly by clicking on the phone number. To do so, we need to first ask for this permission to the user.

name: A Google user
review: I've ditched Waze in favour of HERE WeGo, since I like the Tizen companion that goes on my Samsung Gear S3 watch. Using it in the car, with my 8" tablet, is a bit mixed feeling. It's ok during actual tracking, but what happens when I do a search? --It switches to portrait mode!!! ...which forces me ...Full ReviewI've ditched Waze in favour of HERE WeGo, since I like the Tizen companion that goes on my Samsung Gear S3 watch. Using it in the car, with my 8" tablet, is a bit mixed feeling. It's ok during actual tracking, but what happens when I do a search? --It switches to portrait mode!!! ...which forces me to type sideways!!! HERE, obviously assumes that all devices are installed vertically in a car, but that is not practical, nor safe, for other devices than mobile phones. I happen to use a tablet, which is securely installed above the info-screen. I cannot turn the device, unless I release it from the clamp. Since most(all) other screens and applications follow the tilt-sensor for aligning the screen, why can't you do the same? Reading other reports regarding the same issue, and HERE's non-commitment regarding it, I realise that the application is unfit for car navigation and is uninstalled. I'll keep it for navigating around cities by foot, however.

negative that I found is that it's limited to only bringing up 20

Instead, it just says "merge to Highway 5."  Also, I wish it could provide the information about the turn immediately pending the upcoming one, so it will be easy to know which lane to keep (left-most lane for pending left turn and right-most lane for pending right turn).  Take a long time to "recalculating" new router. Always insist on "going back to the correct route."

name: D Singleton

select the one that suits you. Rerouting is quick. Now I am dropping this 
to 4 stars because there is no apparent way of changing the map detail to 
show names of roads on approach to junctions - the screenshots of the maps 
in the play store advert just don't match the maps available in the app. 
This needs to be fixed so as not to disappoint users.

This creates big confusion when you are actually in the correct Traffic Lane (meant for turning) and you can not go straight and/or U-Turn is not allowed on the traffic signal.

name: A Google user
review: I've been using this app for over 5 years.  Change phone ? I load it on my new phone. Change phone ? I load it on my new phone.  I've used it walking in the countryside - still shows where you are  as it's from a satellite - as long as you have downloaded in my case the whole of the UK and you can get GPS.  - ( Turn your location on your phone on. )   I've used it cycling through forest, countryside. On public transport so I know where I'm getting off.  Though mostly I use it in the car. And it has helped me get all over the country.   If it plays up or gets stuck - which I found on rare occasions, make a written note of any locations it has you want to save and go to settings and clear history.

name: A Google user
review:
This is literally the only navigation app that comes close to Google Maps 
in terms of ease of use. Routing is acceptable, not Google quality but 
passable. Nevertheless there are significant problems that keep me from 
adopting it: A deeply neglected "community" of volunteer mappers whose 
edits ne...Full ReviewThis is literally the only navigation app that comes close to Google Maps 
in terms of ease of use. Routing is acceptable, not Google quality but 
passable. Nevertheless there are significant problems that keep me from 
adopting it: A deeply neglected "community" of volunteer mappers whose 
edits never seem to make it to production and pretty much zero corporate 
engagement. A very cruddy map interface that does not allow a user to turn 
on satellite imagery during a route. Bad gyro predictives that give an 
almost drunk, lurching feeling to the map as opposed to Google's smooth as 
butter gyro interpolation. It's not awful but needs a lot of work and some 
serious effort to engage its community.

name: A Google user
review: Downloaded the app as well as many specific points of interest in Tanzania, Amsterdam, Paris, and Dublin so I could always use it offline.  Although it worked offline somewhat, it didn't work well and I walked many more miles than necessary, many more. Maybe it wasn't able to make a strong connectio...Full ReviewDownloaded the app as well as many specific points of interest in Tanzania, Amsterdam, Paris, and Dublin so I could always use it offline.  Although it worked offline somewhat, it didn't work well and I walked many more miles than necessary, many more. Maybe it wasn't able to make a strong connection to gps when needed? It also sometimes stopped working suddenly and completely disappeared. Not a good thing when you're in an unfamiliar city. The small green indicator of my location  didn't clearly show the direction I was walking was part of the problem. Another is that the verbal command to turn left, right, wherever, wasn't timely, it told me to turn before or after where I needed to turn.  Hence the additional miles I had to walk. Maybe if my location indicator more clearly showed the direction I was walking, I could have seen by the map where to turn. It also would have been really helpful to be able to bring up a city and see all of my saved points of interest, with labels, and my location on the map. Often, I didn't know where I was in a city but wanted to know  where I was and the closest point of interest, such as the closest Starbucks, but the app just doesn't do that.

name: Maury Kaplan
review: I have a Galaxy Note 2 I "retired" when switching carriers a while back. It still works great for everything (but telephony, of course). So I thought I'd try using at as a GPS with HERE WeGo, which had good reviews.  I downloaded the maps for several surrounding states (the full US map is more than ...Full ReviewI have a Galaxy Note 2 I "retired" when switching carriers a while back. It still works great for everything (but telephony, of course). So I thought I'd try using at as a GPS with HERE WeGo, which had good reviews.  I downloaded the maps for several surrounding states (the full US map is more than 6 gb), then took it out for a spin. The map directions worked perfectly, except for when I got to an area where recent major road work moved some intersections and roads around.  The only reason I give this 4 stars out of 5 is that the nice British lady who now lives in my phone would only say to turn here or go straight there, but not actually say the names of the roads.  I assume that is due to the developers going a little light on the speech synthesis by having her not even try to pronounce names along the route.  On a major trip, not saying the road name (as in, "In 100 feet turn left onto Bo Diddley Avenue" vs. "Turn left in 100 feet") could cause one to make a mistake because while driving you can't really look at the map. While upgrading the app to pronounce map things and places would increase the size and processor requirements, I'd jump all over star number 5.

review: It used to be best offline navigation available. However long distance routing does not work any more in offline mode as it used to be. It still work for short distances.    Workaround for long distance: if you are in France/Germany/Large country with separate downloads, make sure you download the w...Full ReviewIt used to be best offline navigation available. However long distance routing does not work any more in offline mode as it used to be. It still work for short distances.    Workaround for long distance: if you are in France/Germany/Large country with separate downloads, make sure you download the whole country.   I still like the APP, but leave just 1 star, so this feedback hopefully gets noticed, since there is no other way to report the bugs.

name: Ricky Beca-Cherrett
review:
Been using this instead of Google Maps for a bit now, and never going back. 
Works with instructions for public transport, walking, bike riding etc as 
well as driving. Suggested routes are better (for me) over long distance 
country drives, with support for routes including or not including dirt 
r...Full ReviewBeen using this instead of Google Maps for a bit now, and never going back. 
Works with instructions for public transport, walking, bike riding etc as 
well as driving. Suggested routes are better (for me) over long distance 
country drives, with support for routes including or not including dirt 
roads, ferries, toll roads, and more. Seems to pick up GPS signals quicker 
in the city, and most importantly, will keep navigating if GPS signal isn't 
accurate due to obstructions, while signalling that the signal is no longer 
100% accurate. I like knowing where it thinks I am, and simultaneously 
knowing that the GPS signal is currently weak. As always, just letting the 
user know is the best UX. Very quick to re-route if you miss a suggested 
turn. I always have it on when driving for the speed alerts (a feature 
Google Maps currently misses entirely). Finally, privacy is much better. 
You can use the traffic option to see what the traffic is like, which 
includes sending your own information off to their servers to also help 
other users, but it's anonymised and to a company who cares about keeping 
your information private. And if you're not comfortable with even that, 
then there's nothing stopping you from turning off the traffic feature, 
which stops your data for traffic being sent off. So far I've had no issues 
with this app on my tablet. For sure, this is my new navigation app for 
good.

review: As an offline map, it's there when you need it. Google Maps is simply better, especially now that you can download maps to run offline, but it's section by section, which isn't bad if you've planned your trips. But to have guidance completely offline, that's a bonus. Not perfect though; adding favou...Full ReviewAs an offline map, it's there when you need it. Google Maps is simply better, especially now that you can download maps to run offline, but it's section by section, which isn't bad if you've planned your trips. But to have guidance completely offline, that's a bonus. Not perfect though; adding favourites is nice, but it seems you need a (free) account. However, I haven't figured out how to edit them, and don't think you can, so if I want to change the name of something, have to delete the old and add the new. Route selection is decent, not always the best, but still good. If you run it in online mode, you do get live traffic - haven't tried it myself so no comment. End of the day, there if I'm in a pinch

review: Really not nice to have to sign in to save locations! Otherwise, the app is good. It allows offline navigation and finds places really fast. Other navigation apps like Osmand allow to save locations without logg...Full ReviewReally not nice to have to sign in to save locations! Otherwise, the app is good. It allows offline navigation and finds places really fast. There's no legitimate reason one would need to sign in to save a location (favorite...). Other navigation apps like Osmand allow to save locations without logging in. No one can really guarantee that accounts won't be broken in, hacked in. It happens even to very protected places like banks, etc. Who wants whoever knowing where we live, where we go, how we go? It's said it's to provide better service... if that's true, I'd rather have the option to have a not so good service, but preserving my safety. Therefore, uninstalled.

This makes finding something in your own collection a nightmare unless the collection contains very few items. There is no waypoint support - most other navigation apps have such feature. Routes made on desktop can't be neither sent to a device nor synchronized. Given that several other navigation apps also provide offline maps while also providing features that Here WeGo lacks, I can't see an actual reason for choosing Here WeGo. The maps themselves are accurate and navigation good, but, please add more features (I'd gladly pay a reasonable subscription fee if previously mentioned features would be added and adds would be removed). Until then I am better off with other navigation apps.

name: Eric Bright
review: This is everything I ever wanted. Itís been a life-saver to me in countless number of occasions when most other competitors, even the big names, failed. For beginners, it has excellent off-line map with accurate information (at least in Canada). Its GUI is amongst the best in any similar app Iíve tr...Full ReviewThis is everything I ever wanted. Itís been a life-saver to me in countless number of occasions when most other competitors, even the big names, failed. For beginners, it has excellent off-line map with accurate information (at least in Canada). Its GUI is amongst the best in any similar app Iíve tried in this category. It gives you plenty of notices ahead of time before critical turns, whereas with the major competitors Iíve missed many turns almost every single time I drove a highway. All in all, this is one of the best offline maps in the market, hands down.

Having said that, it's easily good enough to get you somewhere when offline but now Google maps offers offline navigation as long as you download the area in advance it has limited value.

It showed me a route I've never seen before so that was nice, but it took me through really small towns where the speed limit is 30 then goes to 75 then 30 and so on. review: It used to be a life saver since it was Ovi Maps, but recently after the last few updates I am facing an issue with the collections feature. I am not able to collect any place. Whenever I try to add new collection, it shows a white blank page. Please resolve it guys.

name: J M
review: After having trouble with a new big name navigation device which the manufacturer could not resolve, despite being given plenty of time to do so, I decided to download this app.  I've not looked back.  This puts paid devices/apps to shame.  Search and it finds places effortlessly.  It directs the us...Full ReviewAfter having trouble with a new big name navigation device which the manufacturer could not resolve, despite being given plenty of time to do so, I decided to download this app.  I've not looked back.  This puts paid devices/apps to shame.  Search and it finds places effortlessly.  It directs the user flawlessly.  Speed (calibrated slightly on the low side) is updated as you drive, along with warnings if you go over the speed limit.  Safety cameras are usually pointed out, and there is a good range of planning/driving options.  We drove from the UK to France and this neat app didn't let us down once.  Well done and big thanks for providing a near perfect SatNav app! The Meadows

name: A Google user
review: Needs proper lane guidance/lane assist. With that it really would be a five star app. Still the best of the freebies by some margin but the bug of 'awaiting GPS' needs fixing. Fix these two shortcomings and start charging for the app! If CoPilot can charge £22 and get great reviews when it's simply ...Full ReviewNeeds proper lane guidance/lane assist. With that it really would be a five star app. Still the best of the freebies by some margin but the bug of 'awaiting GPS' needs fixing. Fix these two shortcomings and start charging for the app! If CoPilot can charge £22 and get great reviews when it's simply appalling across the board, and Navigon can do it well but charge £40+ then you could get £25-30 for this app. Navigon and Tom Tom are the best but they cost a fortune. Here We Go really could be right up there with those two if only you had lane guidance and quashed this GPS bug.

name: Mbizozo
review: My only problem with this app is that you can't lower the voice navigation volume without affecting the media volume. So if I'm playing music at a high volume the voice navigation becomes really annoying.  If the developers could change that it would be a great help.

name: Patrick Huhn
review: Good nav app for offline world wide travel. Light on battery and processor. Travel time is calculated quite conservatively. Some annoyances : 1)No navigation via intermittent stop, so if you prefer a detour, you need to set new destination. 2) if searching for POI along the route, the current naviga...Full ReviewGood nav app for offline world wide travel. Light on battery and processor. Travel time is calculated quite conservatively. Some annoyances : 1)No navigation via intermittent stop, so if you prefer a detour, you need to set new destination. 2) if searching for POI along the route, the current navigation has to be cancelled.

name: Bob
review: I've been a fan of Here Maps since first using it on Windows Phone. This version works okay at best. I wish adding favorites was a little simpler and the map graphics look like they came out of 2003. The routing needs to be clearer and there should be rerouting options when there's traffic, the ETA ...Full ReviewI've been a fan of Here Maps since first using it on Windows Phone. This version works okay at best. I wish adding favorites was a little simpler and the map graphics look like they came out of 2003. The routing needs to be clearer and there should be rerouting options when there's traffic, the ETA is too conservative, and occasionally it takes me ways that make no sense at all. And now it seems to be losing the GPS signal way too often. Please put some major work into this. It has too much potential.

review: Generally a very nice app. Beautiful clean interface. Good search features. Does not always choose the most sensible routes and the visual map while driving is ugly and very jerky compared with its competitors. Give us a smooth and pretty map and I shall use it always.

review: I like the app's appearance and speed limits feature. However, the app doesn't suggest in which lanes to move, and it doesn't name exit numbers - so I suffered when trying to navigate around Miami using this app - plain route is not very helpful on highways with lots of exits, and voice commands often come too late. Google maps have ugly design and don't help with speed limits, but they provide near perfect lane/exit assistance, so can't replace them with this product.

It always switches to...Full ReviewUseful, but when I tried updating the offline maps recently, the application would no longer start up.  Now I reinstalled it and all the previouslt maps have been deleted. There also seems to be no feature to navigate in bird's eye view with a route selected and stay that way.  It always switches to 3D fixed camera view when I move. Finally, there are no hands free voice commands.  The best you can do is hit the search bar, hit the microphone button in the keyboard, then speak and select the address with your finger.  That is not suitable thing to do while driving.

review: HERE WeGo is a nice navigation App. However, to access "My Collection" in HERE WeGo one has to sign in to the Internet. Which means one can't use the own POI's without data plan (NOT offline). In fact this App is lacking in my opinion an essential function in order to make it really handy. MAPS.ME f...Full ReviewHERE WeGo is a nice navigation App. However, to access "My Collection" in HERE WeGo one has to sign in to the Internet. Which means one can't use the own POI's without data plan (NOT offline). In fact this App is lacking in my opinion an essential function in order to make it really handy. MAPS.ME for instance stores "My Places" on the device. Once the required maps are downloaded, MAPS.ME it's really completely offline to use. Way better solution for me.

review: The app works pretty well and does its job. Great voice guidance, little interference with driving, be very fast rerouting in case of missing a turn.  However, the two most important features that I find lacking is (a) no lane assistant and (b) landscape support only in navigation screen, everything...Full ReviewThe app works pretty well and does its job. Great voice guidance, little interference with driving, be very fast rerouting in case of missing a turn.  However, the two most important features that I find lacking is (a) no lane assistant and (b) landscape support only in navigation screen, everything else is forced to portrait.  A highly annoying "feature" is the fact that it constantly keeps signing the user out if the device is powered off or offline for a few days. For the signing in again, the user needs to re-type BOTH email address and password. Can't it at least preserve the email address when feeling the need to have the login time out? In addition, this stupid auto-popup "Getting Around" is pretty much nothing I care about. I'm driving by car, not by the public transport lines it suggests. At least allow me to set preferences for stuff to show up there. Also, unfortunately, the app can't make use of Android adoptable storage (installs internally only, can't change map storage to SD card).

OK, the maps are not the most detailed, but whole countries can be downloaded in advance and no data connection is needed for navigation. The only thing that stops me giving 5 stars is the ...Full ReviewI used the old Here (formerly Nokia) maps on Symbian devices for many years and was always very happy with it. OK, the maps are not the most detailed, but whole countries can be downloaded in advance and no data connection is needed for navigation. The only thing that stops me giving 5 stars is the lack of street names in the voice directions. This was available in previous versions, but no longer appears to be available.

name: A Google user
review: This used to be my 5* go to app for both offline and online navigation. Until a year or so ago. But the maps in my area  still display old shops/ landmarks from a year or more ago. Also the green circle on pedestrian navigation is nowhere near the blue line of the route to take. It used to be bang o...Full ReviewThis used to be my 5* go to app for both offline and online navigation. Until a year or so ago. But the maps in my area  still display old shops/ landmarks from a year or more ago. Also the green circle on pedestrian navigation is nowhere near the blue line of the route to take. It used to be bang on the line and stayed there without drifting. Finally, when driving, the arrow seems to lag and is always slightly behind where your vehicle actually is. It's very easy to pass turnings as they appear just as you are passing them. Hope these issues can be addressed.

name: David Mitchell
review: Have used this app for navigation in the UK, Europe and the USA and it has always been accurate. I previously used a version on a Windows phone was better but recent upgrades on the Android version are making it more like the Windows version. One big disappointment is the fact that the app no longer...Full ReviewHave used this app for navigation in the UK, Europe and the USA and it has always been accurate. I previously used a version on a Windows phone was better but recent upgrades on the Android version are making it more like the Windows version. One big disappointment is the fact that the app no longer allows storage of maps on SD card but instead saves them to internal memory on the device. This has recently led to an issue where I could not upgrade the system software on my device as it said there was insufficient memory available. I have had to remove my maps to apply the upgrade and then try to reinstall the maps. For some reason the map downloads are only getting to about 2% and then hang. I have managed to download the UK map after multiple attempts over several days. If Here can resolve problem of storing maps on SD card again then I would give the app a higher rating.

It took me several times to such a routes and such a roads, that was totally illogical and I would not have called that a road (even unpaved road was disabled). I am deeply saddened, that after almost 10 years of happy user experience, I need to look for an alternative. Not good job guys. :/

On a positive note, the voice direction is good, & 3D lan...Full ReviewSome locations are wrong or off, and some routes go through one way streets. It seems to have a problem with pinpointing where I am on the map unlike waze, & sometimes it suddenly switches to another route even when I chose a different route. On a positive note, the voice direction is good, & 3D landmarks are impressive. I'll keep it as a backup.

name: Dougie Price
review: This is the best app for maps you can get. You can download all the maps offline by choosing entire countries to download, and it saves all shop locations offline as well. When travelling without Internet access I could type in "shop" and it would give me directions to the nearest one without fail! ...Full ReviewThis is the best app for maps you can get. You can download all the maps offline by choosing entire countries to download, and it saves all shop locations offline as well. When travelling without Internet access I could type in "shop" and it would give me directions to the nearest one without fail! Seriously impressive.

name: Tony C
review: HERE WeGo ... is an excellent app for navigation, in particular for offline navigation. You can download entire states, countries or continents to your phone/device while you have free wifi (at home for example); then, you can throw away the SIM card if you like, because you won't need 3g or 4g data...Full ReviewHERE WeGo ... is an excellent app for navigation, in particular for offline navigation. You can download entire states, countries or continents to your phone/device while you have free wifi (at home for example); then, you can throw away the SIM card if you like, because you won't need 3g or 4g data to navigate when you start your travels. HERE WeGo is light years ahead of apparent competitors.  If you want true offline navigation that just works, then look no further than HERE WeGo ...

You can choose the maps you want to download, it displays yo...Full ReviewI used to be an avid user of Google Maps but it lacks some standard features you normally find on a dedicated sat nav.  We used to use Here Maps on our work phones so I was pleased to see it available on android.  What can I say, it works. You can choose the maps you want to download, it displays your speed, offers over speed and speed camera alerts, multiple route choices and is highly configurable.  Also, and just as importantly, it has always been stable even on a long run.

name: Eddie Marrett
review: This app would would be useful for just the maps alone: they're of a far better quality than Google Maps making them much easier to use, especially in cities. But then there is another amazing feature: offline maps. The app allows you to download maps for a whole country (and save them to sd card) w...Full ReviewThis app would would be useful for just the maps alone: they're of a far better quality than Google Maps making them much easier to use, especially in cities. But then there is another amazing feature: offline maps. The app allows you to download maps for a whole country (and save them to sd card) which is really helpful if you're going on holiday and needs maps but don't have coverage. Also the in-app advertising isn't to annoying either!

name: Skand Hurkat
review: I really want to like this app. I used Here when it was Ovi maps on my Nokia phone. I like that this app offers offline navigation and speed limit warnings. And it seems better from a privacy perspective than Google maps.  That, however, is where the praise ends. This app is horrendously slow to tak...Full ReviewI really want to like this app. I used Here when it was Ovi maps on my Nokia phone. I like that this app offers offline navigation and speed limit warnings. And it seems better from a privacy perspective than Google maps.  That, however, is where the praise ends. This app is horrendously slow to takes for ever to load and search, and sometimes stops responding and crashes while I'm driving.  The lack of lane guidance and android auto integration are other major absences in the feature list. And as much as I hate to say this, Google maps' voice instructions are just so much more helpful when navigating complicated interstate on and off ramps in quick succession.

name: A Google user
review: Previously fantastic. However the latest version persistently runs in the background, rapidly draining battery even when it hasn't been used for days. However the latest version persistently runs in the background, rapidly draining battery even when it hasn't been used for days. Even worse, it auto starts at boot, with no way to stop or exit the app - if you force stop in the app manager, it restarts! A shame to see a very useful app effectively become malware - hopefully the developers will do something about this at some point.

name: Anuj Singhal
review: There was a time when I used to prefer Here maps over Google, the main reason was offline navigation with other smaller things like more voice guidance options, 3D rendering of landmarks, etc.  Over a period of time, Google maps has improved tremendously and I feel this app lagging behind.  Some of ...Full ReviewThere was a time when I used to prefer Here maps over Google, the main reason was offline navigation with other smaller things like more voice guidance options, 3D rendering of landmarks, etc.  Over a period of time, Google maps has improved tremendously and I feel this app lagging behind.  Some of the reasons why I prefer Google maps now are: 1. Much better mapping data, Here might have fully downloadable maps but what's the point if they take forever to update.  2. Google beats Here in traffic data accuracy and hence the ETAs on Here are way off the time that it actually takes to drive to any place.  3. There is no real time alternative faster route options given. (due to poorer) traffic data I think.  4. Bluetooth implementation could be better.   All in all, if data consumption is an issue, stick to this, else use Google maps

Only gripe is could do with a detour function. I often travel at night in the UK when many motorways are closed for repairs. review: I've used this app for years on my WP8 Nokia. The android version has some welcome additions, but what it lacks is HFP for Bluetooth connection in the car so it can interrupt radio or CD as it does on WP8. The addition of this would make the app market leading. I've downloaded a 3rd party app - Audi...Full ReviewI've used this app for years on my WP8 Nokia. The android version has some welcome additions, but what it lacks is HFP for Bluetooth connection in the car so it can interrupt radio or CD as it does on WP8. The addition of this would make the app market leading. The map of Catania contains many errors, e.g., one way streets are not correct, or even blocked streets for cars are not listed! The same goes for Siracusa, Noto, .... 3. The routing off or online is far from optimal: In the cities the App navigates you into very very small roads, which may be shorter in terms of distance, but you have to drive so carefully and slowly that this won't be beneficial at all. Database is still woefully inadequate. Still no multi-leg routes. Still very cumbersome to choose the start point directly on the map. No way to contribute to the map directly from the app.  On the positive side:  Great public transport support Clean, easy to read UI. Speedo and speed warnings

review: I am from India. Was using Navimaps for over two years. But with latest updates couldnt store the offline maps on external sd card drive. Was using Navimaps for over two years. But with latest updates couldnt store the offline maps on external sd card drive. So, to free up my phone's rom i switched over to here maps. Now I can store maps on sd card. They are huge ... 2.5 Gb for whole India. Whereas it was only 1.2 Gb in Navimaps. I guess Here map contains more details. Routes are pretty accurate with lots of markers. Still, would love to get periodic updates for the maps, so they continue growing in coverage, accuracy and details. Another feature I liked was to get sattelite view of the map from inside the app itself (requires data connection though).  Finally, I will like to say Thank you here maps for making life easier for those of us who travel a lot and to distant places. Please give regular map updates so as to include more details.

name: Charudatt Gupte
review: Truly the best navigation app that I have used. A big benifit over google maps is the offline ablility and accuracy.   I did my recent holiday in Europe using the here maps. Paris, Amsterdam, Brussels and Luxembourg, besides a few places like Ghent and Bruges.   I did not know any streets or roads i...Full ReviewTruly the best navigation app that I have used. A big benifit over google maps is the offline ablility and accuracy.   I did my recent holiday in Europe using the here maps. Paris, Amsterdam, Brussels and Luxembourg, besides a few places like Ghent and Bruges.   I did not know any streets or roads in these cities. Here maps took me to the precise location either in walk mode or by car.   On one occassion the taxi driver lost his way in Brussels and used Here maps to reach my destinantion. On another occassion google maps got the destination all wrong and Here maps to the rescue.   Kudoos to the team. Highly recomended for all users. It's one app everyone must have.

name: Annie Wong
review: I do 50% business travel and I often travel on no cell site routes.  I have tried several off line maps and this is the best free app by far.  Even during off line mode, the results are very accurate.  I was able to find popular attractions by searching the attraction names. I have searched by addre...Full ReviewI do 50% business travel and I often travel on no cell site routes.  I have tried several off line maps and this is the best free app by far.  Even during off line mode, the results are very accurate.  I was able to find popular attractions by searching the attraction names. I have searched by address and the routes came right up.  This is one feature that many other off line maps don't do well as the apps can't locate the address when in off line mode. The entire US map takes about 6GB.  I guess this is what make this app more accurate than the other apps as other apps are between 1 to 2 GB file size, the larger the file size, the higher the accuracy. Unless, you have a high storage phone or have the ability to store files on a micro SD card, the large file size could be a problem.  I have a Honor 5X, and the phone allows me to store map data on the SD card and it worked out quite well.    Anyway, this is a life saver for road warrior like me.  I feel much more prepare and at ease now that I know I can find my way around at the no cell site areas.

name: A Google user
review: I have used Here Maps from Windows Phone 8.0 up and on Android 4.4 up for real estate.  Clients properties and showings grouped in different Collections.  Only real problem I've had was a late 2014 update that caused collections to not load.   But, now, with it installed on two different Moto Z Forc...Full ReviewI have used Here Maps from Windows Phone 8.0 up and on Android 4.4 up for real estate.  Clients properties and showings grouped in different Collections.  Only real problem I've had was a late 2014 update that caused collections to not load.   But, now, with it installed on two different Moto Z Force Droids, it causes the GPS location to jump to different locations (200-500 yards away).  It is not consistent.  Sometimes it locks steady, sometimes it jumps.  If I uninstall the software, GPS location locks on and stays. The Moto's have Android 7.0.

name: Tim Nielsen
review: The navigation part is great, and the offline capability is priceless for travels.  The download feature is having some issues though. I am not able to download offline maps, if I use my SD card as storage location. It will simply say "Preparing your maps" forever. No warning or errors. If I switch ...Full ReviewThe navigation part is great, and the offline capability is priceless for travels.  The download feature is having some issues though. I am not able to download offline maps, if I use my SD card as storage location. It will simply say "Preparing your maps" forever. No warning or errors. If I switch to internal storage, it downloads right away. I would rather use my cheap SD storage for something like this though. I cannot find anything regarding storage permissions, and my other apps are able to write to SD card without issue. Asus Zenfone 2 on MM. Edit. Suddenly, for unknown reasons, download starts right away. Still took 2+ hours to download Denmark(250MB) though.

name: Pete Shea
review: So frustrated. Thought I might have found a google maps replacement, but this has a fatal flaw. Overall, this seems very good, but there is no way to do waypoints so I can make a custom route, which I do on pretty much every trip. In theory, the online web map supports syncing routes to the app, but...Full ReviewSo frustrated. Thought I might have found a google maps replacement, but this has a fatal flaw. Overall, this seems very good, but there is no way to do waypoints so I can make a custom route, which I do on pretty much every trip. In theory, the online web map supports syncing routes to the app, but in actuality, that doesn't work either. So the web map is awesome at the desk, but useless for phone navigation.  Google maps remains the only viable option I've found and it doesn't support offline maps.  Good: Great maps, both visually and detail Fast routing Shared collections on app and web can only download all of N America, not by state, so huge  Bad: no waypoints on app syncing routes does not work

review: The best satnav app out here in Google play. I have a previous experience from using Here drive+ from a windows phone and wasn't truly sure if this app will live up to my expectations. Fortunately it did and better in a way as it gives you different routes as what Google maps does. This has built in...Full ReviewThe best satnav app out here in Google play. I have a previous experience from using Here drive+ from a windows phone and wasn't truly sure if this app will live up to my expectations. Fortunately it did and better in a way as it gives you different routes as what Google maps does. This has built in traffic info which lets you know if there will be a delay along the way unlike some other satnav apps that you have to pay more to avail these tupe of features. If you want a straightforward and all inclusive satnav app, believe me this is the best out here without breaking your bank.

name: A Google user
review: Concerned about the ADS. Not sure how bad it's going to get but if it's going to be all downhill for this great map service if it gets worse. ADS, AD BANNERS etc are things that will ruin the look and feel of this service. Time will tell.  For now, still a great option to have if a navigation servic...Full ReviewConcerned about the ADS. Not sure how bad it's going to get but if it's going to be all downhill for this great map service if it gets worse. ADS, AD BANNERS etc are things that will ruin the look and feel of this service. Time will tell.  For now, still a great option to have if a navigation service is what your looking for. The ability to be alerted once you reach a certain speed is something this had for a while. But that AND the app to show you what the speed limit is is a huge pro. Not all nav services show or tell you what the speed limit is. This does, and it's one of my favorite features. That and the accurate maps of course.  Inside building navigation is something else I look forward to expanding and growing.

name: Fritz Pinguin
review: I really like the navigation part, and the quick reaction of the app whenever you decide to go your own way. Recalculation of the route is much faster than in any other app of it's kind.  While it does it's job quite well, there is one major flaw: You cannot export/import POIs without big hazzle. Th...Full ReviewI really like the navigation part, and the quick reaction of the app whenever you decide to go your own way. Recalculation of the route is much faster than in any other app of it's kind.  While it does it's job quite well, there is one major flaw: You cannot export/import POIs without big hazzle. The predecessor (Nokia Maps, OVI Maps) could easily read lmx files, but HERE does not. Editing of POIs within the app is quite limited, more or less you can just edit the "collection(s)" to which the POI belongs.  I also liked the UI of Nokia Maps more...  I plan to go to Hong Kong in a few weeks from now. Thanks god I still have my running Nokia N8 with Ovi Maps on it. Why are the Hong Kong/China maps dropped from HERE?

The only improvement I would make is dynamic rerouting for traffic (at the moment you select ...Full ReviewI bought a win8 mobile to enjoy the huge benefits of free offline worldwide maps. The only improvement I would make is dynamic rerouting for traffic (at the moment you select your route at the start of the journey with traffic info, but it doesn't offer alternatives if the traffic changes). Still, great reliable app. I am very happy.

I work in different locations all the time, and I was unfamiliar with this place. I became infuriated already being late, in addition to that I was seconds away from throwing my phone off the petrol station wall. I remembered I had this app installed because it was recommended to me. I gave it a try since at this point I had nothing to lose. The GPS location on the phone correlated with my location on the road. I arrived at the place an hour late, but I only ever reached there because of this app. Thank you very much.

name: Bill Topp
review: This is clearly a powerful app.  However I (68 year old formerly tech savvy) did not at all find it intuitive to use.  For instance the first time I tried to use it there were no voiced instructions, just arrows.  The second time there was voice, the third time again no voice and different arrow pre...Full ReviewThis is clearly a powerful app.  However I (68 year old formerly tech savvy) did not at all find it intuitive to use.  For instance the first time I tried to use it there were no voiced instructions, just arrows.  The second time there was voice, the third time again no voice and different arrow presentation from the first.  I could find no menu to control either and swiping did whatever but wasn't intuitive either.  I've uniinstalled it and am going to try Waze.  btw I've got a Moto-X android phone purchased when that was owned by Google.

name: Usman Burki
review: I use it always but can improve This is my app of choice while driving (Samsung S7 Edge) but, as compared to Google's similar app it has two areas of improvements (1) movement (car location) as one drives isnt as fluid and real time on map (2) no shortcut to partially mute voice navigation or switch to alerts only. Only option is ...Full ReviewThis is my app of choice while driving (Samsung S7 Edge) but, as compared to Google's similar app it has two areas of improvements (1) movement (car location) as one drives isnt as fluid and real time on map (2) no shortcut to partially mute voice navigation or switch to alerts only. Only option is to either go to settings menu or to completely mute off music sound. This is not good when one is listening to music via bluetooth in car and driving (have to stop car by the side to change setting)
