name: Feng Li
review: Best offline map ever!  I started using OVI map(predecessor of Here Map) with my first cellphone Nokia C5-00. I was totally amazed by the useful functionality and nice UI.(3D rendering was not common at that time).  I came to the US in 2015, I started to use google map, but there is no offline map i...Full ReviewBest offline map ever!  I started using OVI map(predecessor of Here Map) with my first cellphone Nokia C5-00. I was totally amazed by the useful functionality and nice UI.(3D rendering was not common at that time).  I came to the US in 2015, I started to use google map, but there is no offline map in it by default.   Later I bought a Garmin GPS. It works like a charm when I go to other states and never out of service even in countryside. However it is too large, not intelligent enough I don't like the old-fashioned style.   Finally a idea came to me, why not use my retired HTC one as a navigation tool and media center?  It I searched Google Play for 'nokia map' and I got this. Great improvements are taken place in this product and it is still the best offline map for me!    Speed alert is quite useful.

review: Great navigation! A lot of features. I'm a little surprised how for a free app it can have so many things. I'm still missing a couple of features though. name: Roman Yepishev
review: A decent navigation system that could do so much more. *** Pros: Offline turn-by-turn navigation with regular map updates. An impressive number of POIs and quite good building coverage in major cities. Minimal interface makes it fairly easy to use and speed limit warnings are a helpful addition. Map...Full ReviewA decent navigation system that could do so much more. *** Pros: Offline turn-by-turn navigation with regular map updates. An impressive number of POIs and quite good building coverage in major cities. Minimal interface makes it fairly easy to use and speed limit warnings are a helpful addition. Map Creator (web only) allows submitting changes that are (eventually) reviewed by Here experts and then get added to the new map release. Glympse support is also included, so you can share your location with somebody. *** Cons: If you live outside of a major city, you will most likely have no buildings rendered around, making your travel in a field of nothingness with POI markers a mile away from their actual locations. While Here knows about turn lanes and destination signs, they won't display this in the application (probably, to avoid competition with their clients - Garmin, iGO in the US, Sygic for trucks, Telenav for in-car navigation). Traffic display is bearable, but Navmii shows it much better, followed closely by TomTom Go.

The routing also seems to have gotten slightly worse - frequently it guides me to an end-point that is 1/4th mile away from the actual destination. The publisher needs to bring back the lost functionality.   ***************** My Previous (2015) review:  App can be used in both online and offline mode. Complete country maps can be downloaded before travel, eliminating the need for expensive roaming plans for mobile data. Also, since a cellular data connection is not needed, you can get navigation coverage even in out-of-the way places. Finally, routing is rather good and this solution replaces a dedicated navigation unit. I would even be willing to pay for this if it were to be no longer free. One suggestion - please integrate this app with "Contacts".

name: Kare Gundersen
review: Until recently I had  HERE offline walk navigation with voice (and spoken street names), but now there's only a stupid knocking sound when the program wants you to turn. This means that you need to drag the phone out of your pocket, open it and look at the screen in the rain (It will rain), where yo...Full ReviewUntil recently I had  HERE offline walk navigation with voice (and spoken street names), but now there's only a stupid knocking sound when the program wants you to turn. This means that you need to drag the phone out of your pocket, open it and look at the screen in the rain (It will rain), where you previously got the instructions right in your headphones. Driving mode works perfectly with voice and all on my Samsung Note 4, but I need walk mode! What really disappoints is that nobody at HERE responds to questions about that matter. I've left inquiries at the HERE  site \ blog, sent them from the phone as feedback etc. No response. Still, it is the best navigation program available. Looks good, reliable etc. The offline mode is great.  Give me voice in offline walk mode, and I'll give you 5 stars.

name: A Google user
review: In busy urban traffic, this is a POS. Each maneuver is a separate instruction. For example "take the exit" may put you onto a six lane exit, 3 left, 1 straight, 2 right. It's not until the last 100 yards that you get "Turn right/left". Across 5 lanes of traffic and the signal queue? Sure... Then aft...Full ReviewIn busy urban traffic, this is a POS. Each maneuver is a separate instruction. For example "take the exit" may put you onto a six lane exit, 3 left, 1 straight, 2 right. It's not until the last 100 yards that you get "Turn right/left". Across 5 lanes of traffic and the signal queue? Sure... Then after the left/right onto a 5 lane boulevard you get "Turn left/right in 300 feet". Uh-huh, across 4 lanes of traffic...  The appropriate instruction should be "Take the exit, then turn right/left at the traffic light, then turn left/right in 100 yards."  Oh, and The Voice will frequently forget how to say any distance, so the instruction might be "In _____ miles take the exit." Could be 1 mile or 200.  Unless you are a daredevil that keeps one eye on the phone and one eye on traffic, this app is a dangerous POS.

name: Mark Needham
review: Used this app for a road trip in southern Iceland. It was superb both the app and the trip!. I downloaded the whole of Iceland to my phone and it worked offline without any trouble whatsoever. I picked out all the places we wanted to see in advance and stored as favorites. Once I thought that it was...Full ReviewUsed this app for a road trip in southern Iceland. It was superb both the app and the trip!. I downloaded the whole of Iceland to my phone and it worked offline without any trouble whatsoever. I picked out all the places we wanted to see in advance and stored as favorites. Once I thought that it was taking me a long way round so I went the way I thought we should be going but it was correct, It was a dirt track which you are not insured to travel on. It even picked out two speed cameras (bit surprised they were any in Iceland). Only thing that's missing, and I find it really useful in the UK on my usual app, is an indication of any delays on your route. My existing app shows a bar of the journey coloured green, amber or red for the traffic conditions ahead which you can set for a distance. Overall very good.

The recent update says it finds and plans routes better but it actually calculates routes slower than it did before the update. review: Great idea, implementation could use some work. Downloading offline maps, **which is the whole point of this application**, fails often, and with no explanation.  Moreover, after download failure the app often doesn't free up the storage space of the partially downloaded maps.  So unless you're like...Full ReviewGreat idea, implementation could use some work. Downloading offline maps, **which is the whole point of this application**, fails often, and with no explanation.  Moreover, after download failure the app often doesn't free up the storage space of the partially downloaded maps.  So unless you're like me and you use a file browser to go and manually deleted the partially downloaded cache of map data, it's permanently lost storage on your device.  You need to trust an app like this to work when you need it.

review: I have used this app for more than 4 years now, and it was a great app until recent changes that came with the rebranding to 'Here WeGo'. While they added functions with limited use (like car sharing search), quality control has gone down the gutter. Be prepared that every update may break something...Full ReviewI have used this app for more than 4 years now, and it was a great app until recent changes that came with the rebranding to 'Here WeGo'. While they added functions with limited use (like car sharing search), quality control has gone down the gutter. Be prepared that every update may break something. After one update navigation search wasn't working any more because it could not find GPS signal, then there were frequent crashes. After one recent update all my downloaded maps were suddenly gone. Now after an update, downloading new maps doesn't work any more.   UPDATE 10/10/16: According to other sources the re-branding broke the update path, I uninstalled and reinstalled the app and then re-downloaded all maps. It has worked stable for 4 days now, will monitor how it continues. But I don't like being part of the new involuntary Alpha Tester community for Here.

name: Ivan Grnja
review: Great App with tons of features. "City Navigation" in the name is completely misleading, this one App combines all of the functionality of the HERE suite formerly available on Windows Phone. Highlight feature is definitely free offline maps + turn-by-turn navigation. TomTom, Copilot and Navigon don'...Full ReviewGreat App with tons of features. "City Navigation" in the name is completely misleading, this one App combines all of the functionality of the HERE suite formerly available on Windows Phone. Highlight feature is definitely free offline maps + turn-by-turn navigation. TomTom, Copilot and Navigon don't offer this for free (beyond the test period) and Google Maps can only store small, square area of the map offline. Therefore I find HERE to be the most complete package for offline navigation, that is available for free and uses decent map data.

name: Bob Newman
review: Love it for best of breed off-line maps Fabulous off-line maps, far superior to Google Maps attempt, can be counted on for navigation in the boonies where there's no cell signal, and that keeps you safe. Depicts the right level of detail at any zoom level. Far better than other off-line map apps that use open street maps (at least in the ...Full ReviewFabulous off-line maps, far superior to Google Maps attempt, can be counted on for navigation in the boonies where there's no cell signal, and that keeps you safe. Depicts the right level of detail at any zoom level. Far better than other off-line map apps that use open street maps (at least in the USA). Better than Google at identifying dirt roads, but room to improve. I don't get what the "City Navigation" name tag is all about, but Here should focus on where it excels, and that's off-line maps.

review: Good map with issues Pros. Offline navigation is smooth and fast. Option language voice feels customize needs.  Cons. No offline maps for China, Japan, South Korea. name: Michael Chen

I first started using this because I was on WP, so I'm very glad to see it available on Android too. Public transit features still require an internet connection, which I feel could be improved. Currently, I've only been using it in large, populated cities in North America, so I've yet to see if there are gaps in the data.

Probably still the most reliable free GPS.

name: Brian gillespie
review: I have used this a number of times now (including abroad) and everything works great and i would love to give this a 5 star review  However, I have now started using an old Samsung Galaxy Note 8.0 tablet as my in car sat nav (as i used to use my mobile phone) - this is just due to the larger screen ...Full ReviewI have used this a number of times now (including abroad) and everything works great and i would love to give this a 5 star review  However, I have now started using an old Samsung Galaxy Note 8.0 tablet as my in car sat nav (as i used to use my mobile phone) - this is just due to the larger screen so makes things easier to see.  When docked in car, the tablet is always in landscape move, starting up the HERE maps app, i came to realise that the Application forces itself to be portrait when inputting and selecting your destination.  Where as this is not something that would make me stop using the app, it is rather annoying.. making me either undock the tablet or tilt my neck in order to use the application properly before starting my journey   The inclusion of a landscape mode when inputting destinations would definitely make this a 5 star review, but without that inclusion I am afraid i will have to down grade to 4 stars

review: Best mapping service for travelling For several years Google maps has failed to lock my location, but Here maps has found me each time without fail. review: Great interface. Routing needs improvement. The interface is great, but it needs to allow more user configuration. A quick and easy driving shortcut would be nice to have. The app won't take no for an answer and keeps naggi...Full ReviewThe interface is great, but it needs to allow more user configuration. A quick and easy driving shortcut would be nice to have. Routing needs improvement. The app gives me 2 options to drive home from work, and both routes go through a closed road. The app won't take no for an answer and keeps nagging me to get back to the closed road when I bypass it. This is now my backup app.

name: Les Fairall
review: Offline mode rocks! I admit I am a big fan of Google maps, but downloading their maps for offline use is a pain.  I heard a commercial for this on the radio. Installed the app and maps for state I was visiting that I knew had little to no data coverage in the mountains where I was going to be. This app was a life saver...Full ReviewI admit I am a big fan of Google maps, but downloading their maps for offline use is a pain.  I heard a commercial for this on the radio. Installed the app and maps for state I was visiting that I knew had little to no data coverage in the mountains where I was going to be. This app was a life saver.  Worked perfectly for navigation in offline mode.  Also adds some cool features once online too.

name: Elena Florko
review: My favorite navigator I love this app, very handy UI, useful notifications, speed limit alerts. But quite often during my trip I have to switch to another navigation app if there is a construction area ahead. If I can't follow Here's instructions it simply builds a loop to come back to same spot with problems on a road. ...Full ReviewI love this app, very handy UI, useful notifications, speed limit alerts. But quite often during my trip I have to switch to another navigation app if there is a construction area ahead. If I can't follow Here's instructions it simply builds a loop to come back to same spot with problems on a road. Developers, please add some clever logic, if user ignores Here's instructions build new route.

Without it, it's very easy to take a wrong turn if streets are close together and the app o...Full ReviewChanging my rating to lower by one star due to this app STILL not including street names in turn-by-turn directions.  I don't know how hard that is to do, but I know that every other major nav app does this.  Without it, it's very easy to take a wrong turn if streets are close together and the app only says "turn right in 100 feet' ..   My original review: great app, but it doesn't tell he the street / highway names like all my other nav apps do .. there are places in the KC area that have 2 or 3 exits all piled on top of each other, and when the app just says "take exit to the right' that can lead me to the wrong one .. probably a setting that I have wrong tho .. overall, this is a great app ..

Lo...Full ReviewGood features but unreliable. Sometime it crashes at startup. The map download & update process is awkward if you have several regions stored offline (like all Europe) the progress bar go to 57% in a couple of minutes and then stay there for hours, then 96% and again hours with no estimated time. Looking at the WiFi LED on the router it seems that the download is working fast only when the screen active. If you interrupt the download it has to be restarted from beginning and it leave you SD full of garbage (hundreds of thousands of files !!!).  POI import is missing. Used few times offline and gave me inaccurate routes preferring narrow country roads against main streets and bad position (2km away) of my destination, I had to switch to Google Maps to reach my destination.

review: I've tried several SatNav apps over the years, but none of them come close to how reliable HERE is!  It's my constant go to navigation tool, even when I'm out of signal range, it's no bother as the entire UK map system is in my SD card!  This app has gotten me and my friends out of some sticky situa...Full ReviewI've tried several SatNav apps over the years, but none of them come close to how reliable HERE is!  It's my constant go to navigation tool, even when I'm out of signal range, it's no bother as the entire UK map system is in my SD card!  This app has gotten me and my friends out of some sticky situations (their SatNavs / apps flaked on us, would have been stranded in the middle of nowhere if not for this app!), and is great for finding nearby useful places on route.   It has great coverage info of even the most remote areas of the UK, which I depend on while out traveling in the wilds.  The only constructive criticism I have so far, is it confuses itself with a couple of junctions to come off the M25 (south of Dartford crossing), the voice prompt gives incorrect info, while the map stays true. Thankfully I know that route well, so not an issue for me. That's the only quibble I've had in over 3 years of using this app!
